sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complete construct for phasin secretion together with zinc finger binding sites
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct is designed to exist in a plasmid separate from a plasmid coding for the zinc finger-fused enzymes involved in the PHB enzymatic pathway. This construct codes for phasin targeted for secretion by the Type I pathway as well as the Type I associated membrane proteins HlyB and HlyD. It also contains a repeated sequence that allows ordered binding of Zif268-HIV, Zif23-GCN 4, and "Blues" Zinc fingers.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alex Hatch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: None

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M1013
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Complete Construct for Type I Phasin Secretion
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This construct codes for phasin targeted for secretion with the HlyA signal peptide. It also codes for the HlyB and HlyD membrane proteins necessary for type I secretion. Coding regions are controlled under high levels of constitutive expression.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Alex Hatch
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: None
